%20to%20spend%20less%20on%20interest%20over%20the%20life%20of%20your%20loan%2C%20a%2015-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgage%20might%20be%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20you.%20Because%20these%20terms%20are%20shorter%20and%20have%20lower%20rates%20than%2030-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgages%2C%20you%20could%20potentially%20save%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20in%20interest.%20However%2C%20you'll%20have%20a%20higher%20monthly%20payment%20than%20you%20would%20with%20a%20longer%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22ARM%20Rates%5C%22%3EARM%20Rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERates%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fadjustable-rate-mortgage%5C%22%3Eadjustable-rate%20mortgages%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20higher%20than%20fixed%20rates%20recently.%20Last%20month%2C%20the%20average%20mortgage%20rate%20for%20a%207%2F1%20ARM%20was%206.08%25%2C%20while%20the%20average%20rate%20for%20a%205%2F1%20ARM%20was%206.04%25%2C%20according%20to%20Zillow%20data.%20But%20they've%20increased%20in%20October.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20get%20an%20ARM%2C%20you'll%20have%20a%20fixed%20mortgage%20rate%20for%20a%20certain%20period%20of%20time%2C%20after%20which%20your%20rate%20will%20adjust%20periodically.%20On%20a%207%2F1%20ARM%2C%20for%20example%2C%20your%20rate%20will%20stay%20fixed%20for%20seven%20years%2C%20and%20then%20adjust%20once%20a%20year%20after%20that%20until%20you%20pay%20off%20the%20loan%20or%20refinance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Farm-rates-today%5C%22%3EARM%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20often%20(but%20not%20always)%20lower%20than%20their%20fixed-rate%20counterparts%2C%20making%20an%20ARM%20a%20good%20deal%20if%20you're%20looking%20to%20save%20on%20your%20monthly%20mortgage%20payment.%20But%20the%20risk%20with%20an%20ARM%20is%20that%20your%20monthly%20payment%20could%20increase%20if%20rates%20are%20up%20when%20your%20rate%20starts%20adjusting.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp