nant-21826305%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DA%2520mum%2520who%2520lost%2520her%2CGrade%2520Projects%2520in%2520April%25202022.%5C%22%3EMetro%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%C2%A0During%20her%20back-to-work%20meeting%20with%20Managing%20Director%20Jeremy%20Morgan%20in%20early%202022%2C%20Ms%20Twitchen%20revealed%20she%20was%20expecting%20another%20child%2C%20which%20she%20claims%20caught%20her%20boss%20off%20guard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20the%20meeting%20seemed%20positive%2C%20with%20Mr%20Morgan%20expressing%20enthusiasm%20for%20her%20return.%20However%2C%20Ms%20Twitchen%20testified%20that%20the%20tone%20shifted%20dramatically%20upon%20disclosing%20her%20pregnancy%2C%20leading%20her%20to%20believe%20her%20job%20loss%20was%20directly%20linked%20to%20her%20pregnancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20woman%20said%20that%20when%20her%20maternity%20leave%20ended%20in%20March%202022%2C%20her%20company%20didn't%20reach%20out%20to%20discuss%20her%20return.%20She%20then%20emailed%20her%20boss%20on%20April%204%20about%20holiday%20entitlement%2C%20but%20he%20didn't%20respond%2C%20which%20was%20unusual.%20Ms%20Twitchen%20followed%20up%20on%20April%2011%20and%2018.%20Later%20that%20day%2C%20Mr%20Morgan%20called%20her%20to%20say%20she%20was%20being%20made%20redundant%20due%20to%20financial%20struggles%C2%A0and%20delays%20in%20some%20payments%20to%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20later%20claimed%20new%20software%20was%20being%20installed%20which%20meant%20her%20role%20''would%20no%20longer%20exist.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20tribunal%20ruled%20in%20Ms%20Twitchen's%20favour%2C%20finding%20First%20Grade%20Projects%20liable%20for%20unfair%20dismissal%20and%20awarding%20her%2028%2C000%20pounds%20in%20compensation.%C2%A0Judge%20Robin%20Harvard%20pointed%20out%20a%20significant%20inconsistency%20in%20Jeremy%20Morgan's%20reasoning%20for%20making%20her%20redundant.%20During%20their%20February%20meeting%2C%20Mr%20Morgan%20had%20claimed%20the%20business%20was%20doing%20well