20the%20two%20Mandeeps%20met%2C%20there%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20a%20dry%20eye%20in%20the%20room%3B%20gratitude%20was%20all%20around.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20man%20gave%20me%20a%20new%20lease%20of%20life.%20I%20am%20cured.%20No%20more%20medicines%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Mandeep%20Singh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDKMS%20BMST%20Foundation%20India%20has%20helped%20hundreds%20of%20people%2C%20like%20Mandeep%2C%20who%20were%20waiting%20for%20a%20matching%20stem%20cell%20donor%20to%20get%20a%20new%20lease%20on%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhy%20India%20needs%20more%20stem%20cell%20donors%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20global%20registry%20DKMS%20was%20founded%20by%20Peter%20Harf%20after%20he%20struggled%20to%20find%20a%20matching%20donor%20for%20his%20wife%2C%20Mechtild%20Harf%2C%20who%20was%20battling%20leukaemia.%20She%20was%20told%20that%20the%20only%20cure%20was%20a%20bone%20marrow%20transplant.%20Unable%20to%20find%20matching%20donors%20in%20the%20family%2C%20Peter%20Harf%20founded%20DKMS%20with%20his%20wife%E2%80%99s%20transplant%20physician%20Dr%20Gerhard%20Ehninger%20in%201991.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20there%20were%20only%203%2C000%20registered%20stem%20cell%20donors%20in%20Germany.%20Despite%20registering%2065%2C000%20more%20donors%20in%20the%20first%20year%2C%20Mechtild%20could%20not%20get%20a%20matching%20donor%20and%20passed%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKeeping%20his%20promise%20to%20his%20wife%2C%20Peter%20dedicated%20his%20life%20to%20registering%20donors%20across%20the%20world%2C%20to%20ensure%20that%20no%20patient%20died%20due%20to%20the%20unavailability%20of%20a%20matching%20donor.%20Today%2C%20DKMS%20has%20provided%20over%201%2C20%2C000%20blood%20cancer%20patients%20a%20second%20chance%20at%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FDKMS1-1729230493.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20awareness%20campaign%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FDKMS1-1729230493.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FDKMS1-1729230493-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FDKMS1-1729230493-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FDKMS1-1729230493-150x79.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FDKMS1-1729230493-768x402.jpg%20768w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-371023%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAn%20awareness%20campaign%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EContinuing%20Peter%E2%80%99s%20mission%2C%20DKMS-BMST%20%E2%80%94%20a%20joint%20venture%20between%20DKMS%20and%20BMST%20(Bangalore%20Medical%20Services%20Trust)%20was%20started%20to%20help%20Indians%20find%20potential%20donors%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgco.iarc.who.int%2Fmedia%2Fglobocan%2Ffactsheets%2Fpopulations%2F356-india-fact-sheet.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGlobocan%202022%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Global%20Cancer%20Observatory%20found%20that%20more%20than%201%2C15%2C000%20new%20cases%20of%20blood%20cancer%20were%20diagnosed%20in%202022%20in%20India.%20In%20the%20same%20year%2C%20more%20than%2077%2C000%20Indians%20died%20because%20of%20blood%20cancer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBlood%20stem%20cell%20donation%20serves%20as%20a%20vital%20lifeline%20for%20patients%20battling%20blood%20cancers%20and%20other%20blood%20disorders%2C%20such%20as%20sickle%20cell%20disease%2C%20aplastic%20anaemia%2C%20and%20thalassemia.%20These%20conditions%20impair%20the%20body%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20generate%20healthy%20blood%20cells%2C%20leading%20to%20severe%20health%20complications.%20A%20stem%20cell%20transplant%20offers%20a%20solution%20by%20replacing%20the%20diseased%20bone%20marrow%20with%20healthy%20stem%20cells%2C%20allowing%20the%20body%20to%20resume%20normal%20blood%20cell%20production%20and%20significantly%20improving%20the%20patient%E2%80%99s%20chances%20of%20recovery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20thousands%20of%20patients%20who%20need%20a%20blood%20stem%20cell%20transplant%20to%20get%20a%20second%20chance%20at%20life.%20However%2C%20India%20faces%20a%20significant%20shortage%20of%20available%20stem%20cell%20donors%20for%20stem%20cell%20transplants.%20This%20underscores%20the%20need%20for%20more%20stem%20cell%20donors%20as%20a%20simple%20act%20of%20donation%20can%20save%20a%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPatrick%20Paul%2C%20chief%20executive%20officer%2C%20DKMS%20BMST%20Foundation%20India%2C%20says%20that%20they%20came%20to%20India%20to%20help%20the%20patients%20here.%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20difficult%20to%20find%20matching%20donors%20for%20Indians%20from%20abroad.%20We%20needed%20donors%20with%20Indian%20genetic%20traits%2C%20which%20is%20why%20we%20began%20our%20operation%20in%20the%20country.%20We%E2%80%99ve%20registered%201.5%20lakh%20donors%20in%20the%20country%20so%20far.%20We%20need%20at%20least%2010%20to%2020%20lakh%20to%20help%20the%20patients%20in%20the%20country%20today%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20explains%20that%20their%20mission%20is%20to%20give%20as%20many%20patients%20(with%20blood%20cancer%20and%20blood%20disorders)%20as%20possible%20a%20second%20chance%20at%20life.%20India%20has%20a%20very%20low%20number%20of%20registered%20donors%20compared%20to%20the%20vast%20population.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20over%201.3%20billion%20people%20in%20India%2C%20but%20only%20around%200.09%20percent%20are%20registered%20as%20potential%20stem%20cell%20donors%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20than%20raising%20awareness%20about%20blood%20cancer%20and%20helping%20patients%20by%20registering%20donors%20DKMS-BMST%20helps%20underprivileged%20patients%20access%20stem%20cell%20transplant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201600px)%20100vw%2C%201600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fdkms4-1729230865.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20foundation%20has%20registered%201.5%20lakh%20donors%20in%20India%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fdkms4-1729230865.jpeg%201600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fdkms4-1729230865-300x200.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fdkms4-1729230865-500x333.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fdkms4-1729230865-150x100.jpeg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fdkms4-1729230865-768x512.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fdkms4-1729230865-1536x1023.jpeg%201536w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-371030%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221066%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20foundation%20has%20registered%201.5%20lakh%20donors%20in%20India.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20costs%20of%20such%20transplantations%20are%20very%20prohibitive%2C%20the%20foundation%20also%20provides%20financial%20assistance%20to%20patients%20who%20can%E2%80%99t%20afford%20the%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20runs%20a%20programme%20for%20thalassemia%20patients%20%E2%80%94%20an%20inherited%20blood%20disorder%20where%20the%20body%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20produce%20enough%20haemoglobin.%20Every%20year%2C%20more%20than%2010%2C000%20new%20cases%20of%20thalassemia%20are%20diagnosed.%20%E2%80%9CThalassemia%20patients%20have%20to%20go%20through%20blood%20transfusions%20their%20entire%20life.%20This%20can%20be%20avoided%20with%20a%20stem%20cell%20transplant.%20The%20best%20outcomes%20are%20noticed%20when%20this%20is%20done%20between%20the%20ages%20of%20zero%20to%20seven%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Paul.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20step%20to%20match%20donors%20and%20patients%20for%20stem%20cell%20transplants%20is%20HLA%20typing.%20The%20foundation%20does%20this%20for%20free%20for%20thalassemia%20patients%20and%20their%20families%20in%20India.%20Paul%20says%20that%20they%20have%20done%20HLA%20typing%20for%2010%2C000%20thalassemia%20patients%20in%20India%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20working%20with%20many%20transplant%20centres%20across%20the%20country%20that%20have%20access%20to%20their%20donor%20database%20registry%2C%20including%20donors%20from%20the%20WMDA%20(World%20Marrow%20Donor%20Association).%20%E2%80%9CIf%20a%20transplant%20centre%20has%20a%20patient%20and%20knows%20their%20HLA%20profile%2C%20they%20can%20look%20for%20potential%20matches%20on%20our%20database.%20They%20can%20search%20for%20donors%20worldwide.%20We%20are%20hoping%20for%20our%20donor%20pool%20to%20increase%20to%20help%20more%20patients%20in%20need%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20become%20a%20donor%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20challenge%2C%20and%20the%20foundation%E2%80%99s%20primary%20focus%2C%20is%20increasing%20donor%20registrations.%20%C2%A0Only%2025%20to%2030%20percent%20of%20patients%20find%20matching%20donors%20within%20their%20family%2C%20leaving%2070%20percent%20reliant%20on%20unrelated%20donors%20accessible%20through%20stem%20cell%20registries.%20Ethnic%20matching%20significantly%20boosts%20Indian%20patients%E2%80%99%20chances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHaving%20a%20large%20donor%20registry%20comprising%20people%20of%20Indian%20origin%20will%20ensure%20that%20more%20people%20with%20blood%20cancer%20and%20blood%20disorders%2C%20such%20as%20thalassemia%20and%20aplastic%20anaemia%2C%20can%20benefit%20from%20this%20treatment%20modality.%20If%20a%20well-matched%20healthy%20donor%20is%20available%20to%20the%20patient%2C%20the%20transplant%20outcome%20is%20very%20encouraging.%20The%20success%20rates%20can%20differ%20from%20case%20to%20case%20due%20to%20patient%20and%20disease%20characteristics%20variations%2C%20but%20if%20done%20at%20the%20right%20time%2C%2060%20to%2070%20percent%20of%20patients%20can%20be%20completely%20cured.%20In%20fact%2C%20a%20year%20after%20transplant%2C%20many%20patients%20can%20lead%20near%20normal%20lives%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Dr%20Sunil%20Bhat%2C%20director%20and%20clinical%20lead%2C%20paediatric%20haematology%2C%20oncology%2C%20and%20blood%20and%20marrow%20transplantation%2C%20Narayana%20Health%20Network%20Hospitals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201600px)%20100vw%2C%201600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fdkms3-1729230857.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Roman%20Simnizki%20from%20Germany%20donated%20stem%20cells%20to%20Chirag%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fdkms3-1729230857.jpeg%201600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fdkms3-1729230857-300x200.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fdkms3-1729230857-500x333.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fdkms3-1729230857-150x100.jpeg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fdkms3-1729230857-768x512.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fdkms3-1729230857-1536x1023.jpeg%201536w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-371029%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221066%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ERoman%20Simnizki%20from%20Germany%20donated%20stem%20cells%20to%20Chirag.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAny%20healthy%20Indian%20adult%20between%2018%20and%2055%20can%20register%20as%20a%20potential%20stem%20cell%20donor.%20All%20you%20need%20to%20do%20is%20visit%20the%20website%20and%20click%20on%20register.%20You%20will%20fill%20in%20your%20basic%20details%20and%20share%20your%20address%2C%20through%20which%20you%20will%20receive%20a%20swab%20kit%20at%20home.%20%E2%80%9CSwab%20your%20cheek%20and%20return%20the%20kit%20following%20the%20instructions%20on%20the%20envelope.%20The%20swabs%20will%20then%20be%20analysed%20in%20our%20lab%20to%20determine%20your%20HLA%20(tissue)%20characteristics%20%E2%80%94%20this%20is%20how%20we%20match%20donors%20and%20patients%2C%E2%80%9D%20states%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dkms-bmst.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewebsite%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20is%20only%20the%20first%20step.%20Donors%20must%20be%20committed%2C%20emphasises%20Paul.%20If%20you%20are%20matched%20with%20a%20patient%20and%20you%20get%20a%20request%20to%20donate%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20important%20for%20the%20donors%20to%20donate%20and%20help%2C%20he%20adds.%20%E2%80%9CMost%20of%20the%20registered%20donors%20internationally%20are%20Caucasians%2C%20who%20generally%20don%E2%80%99t%20match%20Indian%20genes.%20There%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20leukaemia%20patients%20in%20India%20who%20struggle%20to%20find%20donors%20with%20an%20Indian%20ethnicity%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Paul.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20DKMS%20works%20towards%20registering%20more%20donors%2C%20you%20could%20be%20one%20too.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dkms-bmst.org%2Fregister-now%3Futm_source%3Dother%26utm_medium%3Dcpm%26utm_campaign%3Dbetterindian_article%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERegister%20here%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ce